rules.ruleString: Must have passed 2 (I/W) units in {BEH2032, NEH4001}
Must be enrolled in course version {3892}

unitName: Interprofessional practice in community and hospital settings
description: This unit continues to develop the student's ability to provide health care in community based emergency health and hospital settings. It builds on the model of clinical competence and the context of clinical practice commenced in previous years of this course. It provides context to support the clinical theory unit concurrently undertaken in this semester, BEH3032. Supervised clinical experience is undertaken in ambulance and community based health settings. Hospital experience involves critical care areas, operating theatre, and emergency department.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
